      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> It's not possible to directly query for the capability in userspace, but the Linux kernel [added support](https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/1a50ec0b3b2e9a83f1b1245ea37a853aac2f741c) for querying the extension via getauxval in version 5.6 (in 2020), so this is limited to Linux-only for now.\r\n\r\nThat's the correct way to do it. We might actually want to define `WCAP2_RNG` ourselves instead of checking for its existence, to reduce dependency on compiling with specific kernel version headers (especially relevant for the GUIX release binary).\r\n\r\nCode review ACK. I don't have access to hardware supporting this at the moment so wasn't able to test.",
      "created_at" : "2023-04-27T08:43:57Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/26839#issuecomment-1525147489",
      "id" : 1525147489,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/26839",
      "node_id" : "IC_kwDOABII585a5-dh",
      "performed_via_github_app" : null,
      "reactions" : {
         "+1" : 0,
         "-1" : 0,
         "confused" : 0,
         "eyes" : 0,
